## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Since this is primarily a UI refactoring involving feature additions and visual alignments, we will ensure that `npm run build` succeeds without TS compilation errors.
- Run `npm test` if there are existing tests to verify no regressions occur in refactored components.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the application locally `npm run dev` and log in.
2. Verify that the Sidebar aligns with the 15 requested IA items in Arabic context.
3. Access "Alerts Center", select an alert, and click "Open Case". Verify the flow transitions correctly to the Case Management center.
4. Verify that data persists within a session for "Cases" (mocked via localStorage/state).
5. From the "Attrition" or "Performance" screens, test the "Open Case" workflow.
6. Check role-based access for the `Fairness` and `Users` sections ensuring only authorized users can view them.
